OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FNumber of smokers drops as 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fvaping rises, data shows   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The number of people smoking in the UK 
OL,6, dropped to its lowest level on record  
OL,7, last year but more people were using   
OL,8, e-cigarettes, new figures have         
OL,9, revealed.                              
OL,11,FData from the Office for National      
OL,12,FStatistics found around 13.3% of people
OL,13,Faged 18 or over smoked cigarettes in   
OL,14,F2021, down from 14.0% in 2020.         
OL,16,FBut 7.7% of those aged 16 and over said
OL,17,Fthey used e-cigarettes - compared to   
OL,18,F6.4% in 2020.                          
OL,20,FThe first ONS records on smoking were  
OL,21,Fin 2011 and found 20.2% had smoked.    
